{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-02",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_02_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 2 - Death in the Fog",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 7,
  "page_start_sec": 492.416,
  "page_end_sec": 733.18,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.753,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 492.416,
      "end": 494.04,
      "text": "Schilling didn't pay much attention to it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 494.06,
      "end": 495.62,
      "text": "not knowing anything was wrong."
    },
    {
      "start": 496.28,
      "end": 499.32,
      "text": "He says nobody didn't come out of here during the time it took him"
    },
    {
      "start": 499.32,
      "end": 501.44,
      "text": "to come down from Powell or he'd have seen them."
    },
    {
      "start": 501.75,
      "end": 505.12,
      "text": "The only other way out would be under the billboard on Stockton."
    },
    {
      "start": 505.856,
      "end": 506.84,
      "text": "Nobody went that way."
    },
    {
      "start": 507.32,
      "end": 509.12,
      "text": "The fog's got the ground soggy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 509.16,
      "end": 511.04,
      "text": "and the only marks are where Miles slid"
    },
    {
      "start": 511.04,
      "end": 512.9,
      "text": "down and where this gun here rolled."
    },
    {
      "start": 514.4,
      "end": 515.46,
      "text": "Didn't anybody hear the shot?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 516.16,
      "end": 517.34,
      "text": "For the love of God,"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.5,
      "end": 517.7,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.88,
      "end": 519.02,
      "text": "we only just got here."
    },
    {
      "start": 519.904,
      "end": 520.92,
      "text": "Somebody must have heard it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 521.0,
      "end": 522.04,
      "text": "when we find them."
    },
    {
      "start": 523.04,
      "end": 525.04,
      "text": "He turned to put a leg over the fence.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 526.36,
      "end": 528.2,
      "text": "Coming down for a look at him before he's moved?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 529.312,
      "end": 529.82,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 530.32,
      "end": 530.74,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 531.69,
      "end": 535.66,
      "text": "Tom halted astride the fence to look back at Spade with surprised,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 535.94,
      "end": 536.78,
      "text": "small eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 537.984,
      "end": 538.5,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 539.296,
      "end": 539.92,
      "text": "\"'You've seen him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 540.56,
      "end": 541.94,
      "text": "You'd see everything I could.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 542.51,
      "end": 543.26,
      "text": "Tom,"
    },
    {
      "start": 543.52,
      "end": 544.72,
      "text": "still looking at Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 544.86,
      "end": 547.68,
      "text": "nodded doubtfully and withdrew his leg over the fence."
    },
    {
      "start": 549.48,
      "end": 551.98,
      "text": "\"'His gun was tucked away on his hip,' he said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 552.48,
      "end": 553.64,
      "text": "\"'It hadn't been fired."
    },
    {
      "start": 554.6,
      "end": 557.0,
      "text": "There was a hundred and sixty-some bucks in his clothes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 557.58,
      "end": 558.46,
      "text": "Was he working,"
    },
    {
      "start": 558.56,
      "end": 558.98,
      "text": "Sam?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 559.82,
      "end": 559.92,
      "text": "Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 560.58,
      "end": 561.74,
      "text": "after a moment's hesitation,"
    },
    {
      "start": 562.14,
      "end": 562.6,
      "text": "nodded."
    },
    {
      "start": 563.74,
      "end": 564.16,
      "text": "Tom asked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 564.82,
      "end": 565.26,
      "text": "\"'Well?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 566.11,
      "end": 568.12,
      "text": "\"'He was supposed to be tailing a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 568.12,
      "end": 570.8,
      "text": "fellow named Floyd Thursby,' Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 571.0,
      "end": 571.64,
      "text": "and described"
    },
    {
      "start": 571.92,
      "end": 574.14,
      "text": "Thursby as Miss Wonderly had described him."
    },
    {
      "start": 575.14,
      "end": 575.68,
      "text": "\"'What for?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 576.896,
      "end": 578.56,
      "text": "Spade put his hands into his overcoat",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 578.56,
      "end": 580.98,
      "text": "pockets and blinked sleepy eyes at Tom."
    },
    {
      "start": 582.22,
      "end": 583.74,
      "text": "Tom repeated impatiently,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 583.76,
      "end": 584.96,
      "text": "\"'What for?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 585.79,
      "end": 587.64,
      "text": "He was an Englishman,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 587.74,
      "end": 588.26,
      "text": "maybe."
    },
    {
      "start": 588.68,
      "end": 590.46,
      "text": "I don't know what his game was,"
    },
    {
      "start": 590.56,
      "end": 590.92,
      "text": "exactly."
    },
    {
      "start": 591.88,
      "end": 593.68,
      "text": "We were trying to find out where he lived.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 595.072,
      "end": 597.2,
      "text": "Spade grinned softly and took a hand",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 597.2,
      "end": 599.04,
      "text": "from his pocket to pat Tom's shoulder."
    },
    {
      "start": 600.352,
      "end": 601.02,
      "text": "Don't crowd me.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 602.02,
      "end": 603.58,
      "text": "He put the hand in his pocket again.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 605.04,
      "end": 607.04,
      "text": "I'm going out to break the news to Miles's wife.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 608.2,
      "end": 608.74,
      "text": "He turned away.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 609.1,
      "end": 609.2,
      "text": "Tom,"
    },
    {
      "start": 610.5,
      "end": 611.02,
      "text": "scowling,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 611.18,
      "end": 612.12,
      "text": "opened his mouth,"
    },
    {
      "start": 612.26,
      "end": 614.16,
      "text": "closed it without having said anything,"
    },
    {
      "start": 614.58,
      "end": 615.52,
      "text": "cleared his throat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 615.9,
      "end": 617.36,
      "text": "put the scowl off his face,"
    },
    {
      "start": 617.42,
      "end": 619.54,
      "text": "and spoke with a husky sort of gentleness."
    },
    {
      "start": 621.184,
      "end": 622.74,
      "text": "It's tough him getting it like that.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 623.776,
      "end": 624.7,
      "text": "Miles had his faults,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 624.78,
      "end": 625.86,
      "text": "same as the rest of us,"
    },
    {
      "start": 626.592,
      "end": 628.66,
      "text": "but I guess he must have had his good points,"
    },
    {
      "start": 628.74,
      "end": 629.0,
      "text": "too."
    },
    {
      "start": 630.68,
      "end": 631.28,
      "text": "I guess so.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 632.32,
      "end": 634.22,
      "text": "Spade agreed in a tone that was utterly",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 634.22,
      "end": 635.82,
      "text": "meaningless and went out of the alley."
    },
    {
      "start": 637.68,
      "end": 641.46,
      "text": "In an all-night drugstore on the corner of Bush and Taylor Streets,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 641.7,
      "end": 642.64,
      "text": "Spade used a telephone."
    },
    {
      "start": 643.88,
      "end": 644.98,
      "text": "Precious.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 645.54,
      "end": 646.32,
      "text": "He said into it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 646.36,
      "end": 648.58,
      "text": "sometime after he had given Central a number."
    },
    {
      "start": 649.6,
      "end": 650.36,
      "text": "Miles has been shot.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 651.14,
      "end": 651.4,
      "text": "Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 651.48,
      "end": 652.0,
      "text": "he's dead."
    },
    {
      "start": 652.9,
      "end": 653.82,
      "text": "Now don't get excited.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 654.7,
      "end": 655.12,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 655.936,
      "end": 657.22,
      "text": "You'll have to break it to Iva.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 657.82,
      "end": 658.18,
      "text": "No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 658.24,
      "end": 659.28,
      "text": "I'm damned if I will."
    },
    {
      "start": 660.0,
      "end": 660.84,
      "text": "You've got to do it."
    },
    {
      "start": 661.696,
      "end": 662.52,
      "text": "That's a good girl.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 663.22,
      "end": 664.38,
      "text": "And keep her away from the office."
    },
    {
      "start": 664.76,
      "end": 666.2,
      "text": "Tell her I'll see her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 666.38,
      "end": 666.88,
      "text": "um,"
    },
    {
      "start": 667.06,
      "end": 667.64,
      "text": "sometime."
    },
    {
      "start": 668.5,
      "end": 668.82,
      "text": "Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 668.92,
      "end": 670.22,
      "text": "but don't tie me up to anything."
    },
    {
      "start": 671.264,
      "end": 671.94,
      "text": "That's the stuff.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 673.056,
      "end": 673.5,
      "text": "You're an angel.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 674.36,
      "end": 674.58,
      "text": "Bye.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 677.024,
      "end": 679.6,
      "text": "Spade's tinny alarm clock said 3.40 when he",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 679.6,
      "end": 681.68,
      "text": "turned on the light in the suspended bowl again."
    },
    {
      "start": 682.6,
      "end": 685.6,
      "text": "He dropped his hat and overcoat on the bed and went into his kitchen,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 685.96,
      "end": 688.94,
      "text": "returning to the bedroom with a wine glass and a tall,"
    },
    {
      "start": 688.96,
      "end": 690.16,
      "text": "dark bottle of Bacardi."
    },
    {
      "start": 691.26,
      "end": 692.8,
      "text": "He poured a drink and drank it standing.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 693.6,
      "end": 695.82,
      "text": "Then he put bottle and glass on the table,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 696.28,
      "end": 698.3,
      "text": "sat down on the side of the bed facing them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 698.36,
      "end": 699.2,
      "text": "and rolled a cigarette."
    },
    {
      "start": 700.17,
      "end": 702.4,
      "text": "He had drunk his third glass of Bacardi",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 702.62,
      "end": 705.48,
      "text": "and was lighting his fifth cigarette when the street doorbell rang."
    },
    {
      "start": 706.7,
      "end": 709.08,
      "text": "The hands of the alarm clock stood at 4.30.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 710.44,
      "end": 711.08,
      "text": "He sighed,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 711.1,
      "end": 712.24,
      "text": "rose from the bed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 712.48,
      "end": 714.94,
      "text": "and went to the telephone box beside his bathroom door."
    },
    {
      "start": 716.04,
      "end": 718.36,
      "text": "He pressed the button that released the street door lock.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 719.58,
      "end": 719.96,
      "text": "He muttered,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 720.544,
      "end": 720.98,
      "text": "Damn her!"
    },
    {
      "start": 721.28,
      "end": 723.9,
      "text": "and stood scowling at the black telephone box,"
    },
    {
      "start": 724.18,
      "end": 727.14,
      "text": "breathing irregularly while a dull flush grew"
    },
    {
      "start": 727.14,
      "end": 727.88,
      "text": "in his cheeks."
    },
    {
      "start": 729.28,
      "end": 732.18,
      "text": "The grating and rattling of the elevator door being opened and closed",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 732.4,
      "end": 733.18,
      "text": "came from the corridor."
    }
  ]
}